5.Given a number n, print a sequence of numbers starting from n. Each next number in the sequence is n - 5, and this continues recursively until the number becomes less than or equal to 0. After that, print the sequence in reverse order, adding 5 each time, until it reaches back to the original number n.
Note: You must not use loops.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCECODE :class Solution {
    static void pat(int n,ArrayList<Integer>a){
    a.add(n);
    if(n<=0) return;
    pat(n-5,a);
    a.add(n);
}
    public ArrayList<Integer> pattern(int n) {
        ArrayList<Integer>a=new ArrayList<>(); 
        pat(n,a);
        return a;
    }
}
